column5: A few days ago I was having some work done at my local garage. A blonde came in and asked for a seven-hundred-ten.  We all looked at each other and another customer asked, "What is a seven-hundred-ten?"  She replied, "You know, the little piece in the middle of the engine, I have lost it and need a new one.."  She replied that she did not know exactly what it was, but this piece had always been there. The mechanic gave her a piece of paper and a pen and asked her to draw what the piece looked like. She drew a circle and in the middle of it wrote 710.  He then took her over to another car which had its hood up and asked "is there a 710 on this car?"  She pointed and said, "Of course, its right there."   If you're not sure what a 710 is:                                          Burt
Oil share that one with others thanks!
